   <pb facs="3"/>
   <head>To the Reader.</head>
   <p>VNderstand (Gentle Reader) that this <hi>Treatise</hi> was long since intended for the Presse, but vpon the publishing of that iudicious and sententious <hi>Poem</hi> writ by the worthy decea<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>sed knight Sir <hi>Thomas Ouerberie</hi> neerely con<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>curring with <hi>this</hi> in <hi>Title,</hi> though in matter and manner different: It was thought meete to be re<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>strained till better opportunitie (which is now afforded) might giue it liberty to be reuiued. Receiue <hi>it</hi> then as it was first intended, and so may the Authors labor to <hi>thee</hi> directed, be by thy prayers mutually requited.</p>
</div>
